reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Yongxinsheng DDR3 16GB Kit (4GBx4) Desktop RAM - Enhance Your Computer's Performance

The increased speed results in quicker application launches, faster file transfers, and smoother overall computing experience. It's a noticeable improvement, especially when compared to lower-capacity or slower RAM options.The UDIMM (Unregistered DIMM) design of this RAM ensures compatibility with a wide range of desktop computers. The installation process is straightforward, and the RAM modules fit securely into the motherboard slots. The 2Rx8 dual-rank configuration enhances data access and retrieval, contributing to improved system responsiveness.I appreciate that this RAM kit is non-ECC (Error-Correcting Code) and unbuffered. It simplifies the installation process and makes it compatible with a broader range of systems. Additionally, the 1.5V power requirement ensures efficient power consumption, contributing to energy savings and a cooler operating temperature.Yongxinsheng is known for producing reliable and high-quality computer components, and this RAM kit lives up to their reputation. The modules are well-built and durable, ensuring long-term performance and stability.In conclusion, the Yongxinsheng DDR3 16GB Kit (4GBx4) is an excellent choice for upgrading your desktop computer's RAM. With its impressive capacity, fast speed, and reliable performance, it significantly enhances your computer's multitasking capabilities and overall responsiveness. Elevate your computing experience and unlock your system's full potential with this exceptional RAM kit.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My 8 year old desktop PC has been revived and runs better than ever!
reviews.reviewText: So I was sitting here with an 8 year old HP desktop and pondering a full upgrade. I was running Windows 8, and the stock configuration which included an HHD and 8GB of DDR3 ram. Instead of splurging and spending $500+ for anything decent and new, I decided to do 3 things. 1. Got a free upgrade to Windows 10 which I didn't even realize I could do. 2. Upgraded the hard drive from an HHD to a Samsung SSD. And then 3. Upgraded the ram from 8gb to 32gb of this. And yeah, I think I'm all set for AT LEAST a year, if not more. My computer runs like a dream, it boots up extremely quickly and the lag is gone when I toggle between sites or add new tabs. I don't play any games, but I do often have 10+ tabs open in Chrome with spreadsheets and other things like that. Installation is a breeze, I simply popped out the old RAM and put this in. It took about 5 minutes total. You unscrew the computer case, swap RAM, and you're done. No setup needed at all, the computer recognized it and I was all set. I did have one instance, and only one, where I was toggling between tabs and the computer totally froze up. I just did a hard reboot and it was fine, nothing lost etc. Since I use the computer daily that's pretty good. Make sure your system can handle this RAM but otherwise no sweat, just buy it and enjoy.Looking back, instead of spending $500-1k+ on new hardware, I spend $0 for windows upgrade, and around $65 each for the SSD and 32GB RAM. So about $130 will buy me at least a year if not multiple more years of what I need. A great deal, and by the time I finally do upgrade my hardware (now I'm maxed on RAM since this machine only can handle 32 GB) things will be much more advanced and who knows how much faster and better things will be. Anyway, just buy this RAM, pop it in, and you're good to go. A great value. I would also highly recommend upgrading to a SSD hard drive (my samsung works well) if you have an older machine running an HHD.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars works with Dell Optiplex 9020
reviews.reviewText: My son was complaining about Fortnight freezing up, then the computer started BSODing (Blue Screen of Death) after startup, and would go into a reboot loop after signing in. Every time it would BSOD it would give a DIFFERENT error as to why it was crashing. At first, I thought it was the hard drive I just got from the month before, but after scanning the hard drive for system errors and viruses, I moved on to the next culprit - an NVIDIA driver update (I still haven't ruled that out), but then I went through the DELL system diagnostics partition on the hard drive, and it said that of the four memory modules I had installed (which two were 8GB chips and two were 4GB chips) it was only reading 20GB. The diagnostics determined that I had one bad RAM chip. I decided to replace all four RAMs, since one of the remaining good ones was a lower MHz reading - cant remember right now, it was like a 1200 MHz, while the other two were 1600 MHz. Anyway, for around $50, I was able to replace all four RAM sticks and boost the computer to its intended 32GB, which I verified after start up and running System Information. Me and my son played Fortnight for a good 2 hours, one day, and BeamNG the next day for another 2 hours. He was bragging that his game loaded faster than mine. ,but then again, he has a desktop with a 1080TI gpu, a now fully working 32 GB RAM, and a 650w psu, while I have a laptop with a 1060 and only 8GB RAM. After a couple of days, the RAM seems to be doing great. My 10 year old was able to install one of the RAMs himself. There have been no BSDs or freezing in any of the games since the installation of the memory. I like how the memor is sheilded. This is a good product for the time we have been using it.

Produto de excelente qualidade e deixou o computador muito bom para tarefas pesadas.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This RAM won't set any speed records, but it works straight away and should have great compatibility. I plugged this into a weird Chinese dual X99 motherboard with 2x Xeon E5-2643 v3 CPUs, these shouldn't even be able to support non-ECC RAM, but this stuff just worked straight away no hassle. I can't enable XMP unfortunately to verify that, but I'm quite confident that will work. The heat spreader makes this RAM look and feel far nicer than you'd expect too which is always nice. I've attached a screenshot of CPU-Z showing the timings, again nothing blazingly fast, but plenty enough for a mid range gaming CPU or a light workstation rig like I've installed in. Uses SK Hynix chips too, so the underlying memory chips are a good quality brand, I'd be very confident in the longevity.

Zu viel habe ich mir vorerst von diesen DDR4 RAM nicht erwartet, jedoch wurde ich eines besseren belehrt. Der Direktvergleich hat mich dennoch überzeugt. Bisher habe ich „16GB G.Skill 3200 MHz“ verbaut. Hier habe ich einige Tests und Informationen als Vergleichswert ausgelesen/durchgeführt. Im direktem Geschwindigkeitsvergleich erreichen diese RAM sogar etwas mehr Geschwindigkeit als meine bisherigen RAM. (Bilder). Und auch von der Systemstabilität bin ich zufrieden. Jedoch gibt es dennoch einiges zu klären, die RAM sind keine Dual Ram, lediglich 2 einzelne RAM-Riegel, dies wirkt sich natürlich auf die Performance aus. Mit diversen Tools lässt sich auch nicht so wirklich viel aus den Riegeln auslesen. Zudem Läuft das System bei mir nicht mit den angegebenen 3200MHz. Dies könnte jedoch an Systemeinstellungen liegen. Dennoch bin ich bisher vor allem im Preis/Leistungsverhältnis überzeugt.
